# i18n conventions

## single source of truth

all user-facing text lives in `core/src/i18n/en.ts`. the unified app (desktop + mobile) must use translations from this file. never hardcode user-facing strings in app shell code.

## structure

translations are organized by screen/feature:

| key namespace | scope |
|---|---|
| `home` | HomeScreen labels and buttons |
| `receive` | ReceiveScreen status messages |
| `send` | SendScreen labels, errors, status |
| `session` | ActiveSession labels and actions |
| `approval` | pairing approval dialog |
| `status` | session state display labels |
| `qr` | QR display labels |
| `camera` | camera/scanner messages |
| `common` | shared labels (back, cancel, etc.) |

## adding new text

1. add the key to `core/src/i18n/en.ts` in the appropriate namespace
2. export the type if needed (`TranslationResource`)
3. use the key in the unified app screens
4. never add text directly in JSX — always reference a translation key

## rules

- all translation values are **lowercase** (matches project comment style)
- interpolation uses `{{variable}}` syntax (i18next format)
- error messages must be user-friendly — no stack traces or internal details
- status messages should be concise (< 10 words)
- button labels should be action-oriented ("send", "copy", "end session")

## legacy strings

`core/src/strings.ts` is deprecated. it exists for backward compatibility only. all new text must go in `core/src/i18n/en.ts`. do not add to `strings.ts`.
